SIMPLE: scarecrow
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scarecrow
<hw>Scare"crow`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Anything set up to frighten crows or other birds from cornfields;
hence, anything terrifying without danger.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A <qex>scarecrow</qex> set to frighten fools away.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A person clad in rags and tatters.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>No eye hath seen such <qex>scarecrows</qex>. I'll not march with
them through Coventry, that's flat.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The black tern.</def>
<mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scarefire</ent>⟦br⟧
